description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking to expand your skills and enhance your career to include providing Complex Clinical Care or do you already have Complex Care experience?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;Apollo Home Healthcare is seeking experienced support workers to assist a young gentleman with his care needs.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;We are looking for someone who is dedicated, passionate about their job and enjoys delivering one to one support whilst building positive relationships with our service users and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our service user lives in Darlington with his family and requires a support worker to assist with his care and social needs throughout the weekend.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This gentleman lives on a farm and often enjoys spending time outdoor with the animals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When he is indoors, he likes watching films and playing on his game console.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For this role, it is essential that you have experience supporting service users with neurological conditions and challenging behaviors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Experience Required;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• 6 months previous care experience&lt;br /&gt;• Acquired Brain Injury &lt;br /&gt;• Challenging Behaviours&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have the following shifts available;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• Week Days (8:30am – 5pm)&lt;br /&gt;• Weekend days and nights &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt;This is a personally rewarding role where you can build on your clinical skills and experience, whilst delivering exceptional care and support to our service user and really making an impact on his day to day life.&lt;/p&gt;
